title: Anatomy
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A profile is a JSON object with up to three top-level keys, in any order:

|!Key             |!What it does                                                  |
|`records`        |A template identifying the source array to iterate             |
|`tw-fields`      |Bindings for built-in tiddler fields (`title`, `tags`, …)      |
|`custom-fields`  |Bindings for every other field on the resulting tiddler        |

`records` is mandatory.  `tw-fields` and `custom-fields` are both optional, but at least one of them must contain a `title` binding so each resulting tiddler has a title.  In practice you'll always have `title` under `tw-fields`.

